<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1075] Possible thread hazard in IndexWriter.close(false)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1075</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spinoff from this thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-dev/55391&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-dev/55391&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On reviewing the code I found one case where an aborted merge (from&lt;br/&gt;
calling close(false)) could write to files that a newly opened&lt;br/&gt;
IndexWriter would also try to write to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I strengthened an existing test case in TestConcurrentMergeScheduler&lt;br/&gt;
to tickle this case, and also modified MockRAMDirectory to throw an&lt;br/&gt;
IOException if ever a file besides segments.gen is overwritten.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, strangely, I can&apos;t get an unhandled exception to occur during&lt;br/&gt;
the test and I&apos;m not sure why.  Still I think this is a good defensive&lt;br/&gt;
check so we should commit it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
